cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a method for open-set recognition using deep neural networks and intra-class data splitting. This method is evaluated on image datasets, indicating a focus on computer vision (cs.CV). The use of deep neural networks suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The problem of open-set recognition may also fall under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the proposed method involves regularization, which is a common technique in neural networks and optimization (cs.NE).
